This [example](https://github.com/mlavin/django-selectable/blob/master/docs/lookups.rst#defining-a-lookup) fails under Python 3.x as `filter` is now an iterator with no `len` attribute, which the underlying logic depends on.  Consider switching to a list comprehension.

Current

```
class MyLookup(LookupBase):
    def get_query(self, request, term):
        data = ['Foo', 'Bar']
        return filter(lambda x: x.startswith(term), data)
```

Proposed

```
class MyLookup(LookupBase):
    def get_query(self, request, term):
        data = ['Foo', 'Bar']
        return [x for x in data if x.startswith(term)]
```

